org.dockbox.hartshorn.commands

Interface CustomParameterPattern

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashtagParameterPattern, PrefixedParameterPattern

    public interface CustomParameterPattern
    The type used to provide a argument pattern which can be used to construct types decorated with Parameter, typically done through the DynamicPatternConverter, though this is not a requirement.

      • request

        default <T> Exceptional<T> request(java.lang.Class<T> type,
                                   CommandSource source,
                                   java.lang.String raw)
        Attempts to parse a raw argument into the requested type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The generic type of the target
        Parameters:
        type - The target type to parse into
        source - The source of the command, provided in case the parser is context sensitive
        raw - The raw argument
        Returns:
        An instance of T, wrapped in a Exceptional, or Exceptional.none() if null
